HEADWORD: Plasmogen
<hw>Plas"mo*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Plasma</ets>
+ <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The important living
portion of protoplasm, considered a chemical substance of the highest
elaboration. Germ plasm and idioplasm are forms of plasmogen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

